messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /request/reject/{printRequestID}

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD acceptable: false

- POST acceptable: true

- OPTIONS acceptable: false

- TRACE acceptable: false

- GET acceptable: false

- PUT acceptable: false

- DELETE acceptable: false

- PATCH acceptable: false

Explanation:
- The controller method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/request/reject/{printRequestID}", method = RequestMethod.POST). That explicitly sets the path to /request/reject/{printRequestID} and restricts the mapping to the POST method.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping on RegisterRequestController, so the full path is exactly the method-level value shown above.
- Because the method attribute is explicitly RequestMethod.POST, only POST is allowed according to the code. There is no indication in the source of supporting HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, or "all methods".
- The method signature shows a @PathVariable("printRequestID") long prid, a Principal, and a @RequestBody String motive, confirming that the endpoint expects a path parameter and a request body on POST. The @Secured({"ROLE_ADMIN"}) annotation restricts access to admins but does not change allowed HTTP methods.
